Niger Delta-born artiste, Otuata Emeka Seun aka Styleh has explained why his latest studio effort, ‘What’s up Ibadan’ was dedicated to the new Olubadan and the people of Ibadan. Styleh, who is still basking in the success of his previous single ‘Good Vibes’ said that his love for the Oyo State capital prompted his decision to release a new song for Ibadan.   Lady Donli: Sacrifice I made for my music     Onos Morgan goes for gold in Italy     Yoruba films give more fame, Alesh   Speaking on his latest single, he said: “The main reason I decided to do a song for Ibadan is simply that first of all, I am an African man and I believe so much in culture. I have been to many places in Ibadan and I discovered they have a beautiful culture and the city is also very beautiful”. Continuing, Styleh added: “I love Ibadan people because they are very accommodating, loving, and caring. I might marry an Ibadan lady, the people are nice and they are very accommodating, so I believe they deserve an evergreen song to appreciate them.” Although from the Niger Delta region, Style has worked with top Yoruba music icons including Alhaji Abass Akande Obesere the Late Fatai Rolling Dollar.